Best Buy Co. presently has a consensus price target of $58.50, indicating a potential upside of 6.75%. PCM has a consensus price target of $33.50, indicating a potential upside of 71.79%. Given PCM’s stronger consensus rating and  higher possible upside, analysts clearly believe PCM is more favorable than Best Buy Co..
Dividends
Best Buy Co. pays an annual dividend of $1.36 per share and has a dividend yield of 2.5%. PCM does not pay a dividend. Best Buy Co. pays out 36.5% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. Best Buy Co. has raised its dividend for 5 consecutive years. 
Volatility & Risk
Best Buy Co. has a beta of 1.45, meaning that its stock price is 45% more volatile than the S&P 500. Comparatively, PCM has a beta of 0.95, meaning that its stock price is 5% less volatile than the S&P 500. 
Institutional and Insider Ownership
94.2% of Best Buy Co. shares are owned by institutional investors. Comparatively, 59.2% of PCM shares are owned by institutional investors. 0.8% of Best Buy Co. shares are owned by company insiders. Comparatively, 24.0% of PCM shares are owned by company insiders. Strong institutional ownership is an indication that large money managers, endowments and hedge funds believe a company will outperform the market over the long term.
